'''Service droids''',<ref name="AND">[[A New Dawn (novel)|''A New Dawn'']]</ref> also known as '''servitor droids''',<ref name="Light of the Jedi">''[[The High Republic: Light of the Jedi]]''</ref> '''server droids''',<ref name="DD" /> '''servant droids''',<ref name="DB">{{Databank|aa-9-coruscant-freighter|AA-9 Coruscant freighter}}</ref> '''waitdroids''',<ref name="Expanded Edition">''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story: Expanded Edition]]''</ref> '''attendant droids''',<ref name="Leia Princess of Alderaan">''[[Leia, Princess of Alderaan]]''</ref> a '''serving droid''',<ref name="Wayseeker">''[[The Acolyte: Wayseeker]]''</ref> an '''assistant droid''',<ref name="A Valiant Vow">''[[The High Republic: A Valiant Vow]]''</ref> or '''host droids''',<ref name="Quest for the Hidden City">''[[The High Republic: Quest for the Hidden City]]''</ref> were [[droid]]s designed to serve organics as waiters or waitresses, servants, or in other general service roles. Models of service droid included the [[LEP-series service droid]] and the [[GG-class serving droid]].<ref name="AND" /> At the gala celebrating the bestowment of the [[Raxian Humanitarian Award]] on the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems]]' [[Head of State]], [[Count of Serenno|Count]] [[Dooku]], held on the Separatist [[capital]] [[planet]] [[Raxus Secundus|Raxus]], server droids each held up a tray of appetizers and beverages, including glasses of [[cocktail]]s, which were offered to attendants of the gala. The droids each had metallic bobbed [[hair]] and a short [[Color|red]] dress, and maneuvered deftly through the crowd.<ref name="DD" />

[[Todo 360]] was a [[techno-service droid]] who served the [[bounty hunter]] [[Cad Bane]].<ref name="TVE">''[[Star Wars: The Visual Encyclopedia]]''</ref>

[[Hospitality droid]]s such as [[G1-7CH]] were service droids designed to be kind and caring waiters and waitresses.<ref name="Ultimate Star Wars">''[[Ultimate Star Wars, New Edition]]''</ref>

